All Web Content of the public website of Mittweida. Located at https://www.mittweida.de

defineScope.accessibilitySupportBaseline: Firefox with NVDA and Touchscreen plus Surface Pen
defineScope.additionalEvaluationRequirements:
The report will include a description of the problem and reasons for them. Due to the report being done manually without automated tools, some errors might not have been detected.

Due to the amount of PDFs found amongst the pages, they are not being included in the evaluation, this exclusion also affects PDF forms.

exploreTarget.essentialFunctionality:
Using a searchbar to find information
Provide contact information for public offices
Offer information for citizens
Requesting an appointment
exploreTarget.pageTypeVariety:
Pages exist that are authored by varying people, departments, and other entities.
Pages exist that use varying templates.
Pages exist that use a different layout, design and coding style compared to others.
Pages exist that use different types of content: lists, tables, pictures and videos.
Pages exist that use interactive elements to show further information.
Pages exist that have downloadable PDFs in various places.
Pages exist that change their layout when viewed on a mobile device.
Pages exist that use a varying amount of columns to convey content.

result.description:
Button links that lead to subpages for different school types uses confusing icons. 
Contact information on the right column only utilizes icons to identify different kinds of information.
Some interactable targets do not fulfill the 24 CSS pixel minimum, but due to the spacing exception they pass, barely in thise case.
Button to advance slideshow is only identifiable by shape.
Dropdown information box name and label match due to name text being included in element itself.
Input fields and buttons properly titled.
Two out of three images are not given proper descriptions, third one is given a well written one.

The links labeled 'Mehr lesen' found below the Diashow are part of the same class as the text and can be identified accordingly.

The image links right above the Footer contain a confusing error, the first and second link appear to be either mismatched, or wrong all together, otherwise the image links are properly labeled.
Input fields are labelled with text, but contact information on the right column only utilizes icons to identify different kinds of information.
Autocomplete not functional.

For header, sidebar and footer: Button to return to top of page relies solely on shape. Search bar is marked by symbol only. Unless hovered over, buttons on left sidebar do not convey enough information, and only use shapes.

reportFindings.summary:
The website is based on the TYPO3 v8.7 CMS. Some content appears to be created by people with very limited knowledge of HTML and CSS, especially for the pages which concern topics not part of the city's immediate jurisdiction, like the page for the city's swimming pool. 

Important to note is that there are also several pages which have not been included in the report due to them being either under construction (https://gemeinsam.mittweida.de/, http://www1.mittweida.de/live/) as of the writing of this report, or are not managed/used directly by the city and/or are simply hosted by them (Bibliothek, Amt24).
